    - shipId: K-001
      intent: RESUPPLY
  - day: 3
    narrativeOpen: "The military issued a new directive: effective immediately, all
      cargo bays require secondary scans. Reason \u2014 \"routine security upgrade.\"\n\nNobody
      believes that.\n\nLena didn't show up for work today. Her station has been
      wiped clean, as if no one ever sat there.\n\nYou open the manual and start
      trying to decode those redacted sections. Maybe there's a pattern hidden underneath."
    narrativeCloseDefault: "You checked every detail \u2014 everything passed.\n\nBut
      as you were logging off, you found an auto-generated warning code in the terminal
      log \u2014 a string of numbers you've never seen in the manual."
    narrativeCloseCaught: 'You flagged a ship. The moment you marked it "ENTRY DENIED,"
      its outer hull showed a subtle... texture shift.


      As if something was
      imitating metal.


      Security locked down the berth immediately. No one
      explained anything to you.'
    narrativeCloseMissed: "Night patrol report: temperature sensors in Sector B corridor
      showed an anomaly \u2014 one zone registered a heat signature consistent with
      a human body, but no one should have been there."
    manifestDisplayText: "\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\nARGUS
